Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
  int temperature;
  boolean isRaining;

  public WeatherSimulator() {
    temperature = 20;
    isRaining = false;
  }

  void updateWeather(int deltaTemp, boolean rain) {
    temperature += deltaTemp;
    if (rain) {
      isRaining = true;
      if (temperature < 10) {
        temperature = 5;
      }
    }
  }

  String getWeatherStatus() {
    if (isRaining) {
      return "Rainy and cold";
    } else {
      return "Clear and " + temperature + " degrees";
    }
  }
}",

If 'updateWeather' method adjusts the temperature but no rain is introduced, will the weather status potentially report a temperature other than 20 degrees?
